text: I hope my comment doesn't offend anyone but I have a few words that I would like to say. First and foremost, this movie is such mind-blowing experience where it describes the idea that babies are made from factory thus delivered to their destined place by storks. Which is perfectly fine, judging that this movie is children oriented. But my opinion is, firstly, I feel this movie is objectifying women saying that women equal baby factory. (which is true but don't get mad yet). Secondly, from my perspective, so the orphan teenager is raised by a herd of storks? So should we categorize her as feral children? A bit fucked up, no? And lastly, towards the end, the storks developed feelings for human and the human develops feelings for a human? A pinch of bestiality? But the end of the day, this is a highly rated movie for me. The storyline is fun and interesting.   p.s. before anyone judging my comment. It is my "personal opinion" which I am entitled to.
author: Nicholas Jais
